Xinhua All Media + Beijing Youth Ice Hockey League Helps Winter Olympic Enthusiasm-Xinhuanet December 11, Beijing Dream ING Team Player Pang Yaotian(Middle) Shooting in the game. On the same day, the 2021-2022 season Beijing City Youth Ice Hockey Club League continued to compete in major ice rinks in Beijing. The league was divided into regular season and playoffs. The participating athletes were from U6 to U18. The group was divided into competitive group and selection group, attracting nearly 3600 players from 256 teams in the city. After more than ten years of development,It has become a platform for Beijing youth ice hockey enthusiasts to learn skills and make friends, and to transport excellent players for Beijing City ice hockey team and youth team. The league played a leading role in Beijing youth ice hockey, fueled the enthusiasm of winter Olympic ice hockey, and laid the foundation for the development of Beijing ice hockey in the post-winter Olympic period.
